            "type": "devotion",
            "title": "Daily Devotional",
            "value": "%3Cp%3ENehemiah%20found%20a%20waiting%20enemy%20in%20Sanballat.%20As%20soon%20as%20Sanballat%20heard%20about%20Nehemiah's%20intentions%20to%20rebuild%20Jerusalem%2C%20he%20and%20his%20cronies%20mocked%20and%20ridiculed%20Nehemiah%20(Nehemiah%204%3A1-3).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhenever%20you%20launch%20out%20for%20God%20in%20obedience%20to%20His%20Word%2C%20the%20devil%20will%20be%20right%20there%20to%20tell%20you%20how%20foolish%20you%20are%20to%20even%20consider%20such%20an%20idea.%20He%20points%20to%20those%20who%20have%20tried%20the%20same%20thing%20but%20failed.%20He%20questions%20your%20motives%2C%20accusing%20you%20of%20only%20wanting%20recognition.%20He%20laughs%20at%20you%20in%20hopes%20that%20you%20will%20never%20start%2C%20for%20he%20knows%20that%20when%20you%20are%20resolved%20to%20finish%2C%20%22the%20God%20of%20heaven%20will%20help%20%5Byou%5D%20succeed%22%20(Nehemiah%202%3A20).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EFor%20Nehemiah%2C%20when%20the%20battle%20was%20over%20and%20the%20wall%20rebuilt%2C%20he%20could%20say%20with%20David%2C%20%22Praise%20the%20Lord%2C%20for%20he%20has%20shown%20me%20his%20unfailing%20love.%20He%20kept%20me%20safe%20when%20my%20city%20was%20under%20attack%22%20(Psalm%2031%3A21).%20%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3EWhatever%20you%20are%20doing%20for%20the%20Lord%2C%20%22be%20strong%20and%20take%20courage%2C%20all%20you%20who%20put%20your%20hope%20in%20the%20Lord%22%20(Psalm%2031%3A24).%20Let%20the%20enemy%20ridicule%2C%20scorn%2C%20and%20mock%2C%20but%20God%20will%20have%20the%20last%20laugh!%20%3C%2Fp%3E%0A"
        },
